=== أحمد المحمودي (Ahmed El-Mahmoudy) ===

Email: 
I've been using Linux since 1999, started with Redhat 5.1. Then I tried Debian (I think it was 2.0) in 2000, I was really fascinated with Debian, but then it was too hard for me to use (I recall the setup took me hours). Then I moved on to Mandriva (it was called Mandrake before). Finally I settled on Ubuntu since 2006. I really like the fact that it's based on Debian with its very very rich repository, and yet it is easy to use. I was fascinated that my wifi just worked ! This encouraged me to participate to make Ubuntu (& Debian) even better ! I started contributing to Ubuntu on August 2006. On June 2009, I became a universe contributing developer. On May 2010, I became a MOTU. Also on March 2010, I became a Debian Maintainer.

Contributions: <nowiki>[[https://launchpad.net/~aelmahmoudy/+related-software|Packaging]]</nowiki> for Debian & Ubuntu, bug reporting.
Also active on <nowiki>[[https://launchpad.net/sabily-project|Sabily]]</nowiki> a distribution which is based on Ubuntu.

I think my <nowiki>[[https://launchpad.net/~aelmahmoudy|Launchpad]]</nowiki> page says it all, at least regarding Ubuntu.

Also here is the <nowiki>[[http://qa.debian.org/developer.php?login=aelmahmoudy%40users.sourceforge.net|Debian QA page]]</nowiki>
